      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(slack): support alternate Web API roots",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nPR #95920 was too broad to review because Slack channel extensibility, WhatsApp channel extensibility, and QA Lab Crabline wiring were all bundled together.\n\nThis PR isolates the Slack foundation: the Slack plugin can send every Web API client path to an alternate Slack-compatible API root.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nA mock Slack API only works if all Slack WebClient construction paths use the same alternate root. This threads Slack Web API URL support through send, action, probe, scope, directory, allowlist, monitor, and cached write-client paths without adding Crabline-specific code to Slack.\n\nThe public runtime behavior is env/option based: explicit WebClient options win, otherwise SLACK_API_URL can provide the default API root. OPENCLAW_SLACK_API_URL is intentionally rejected as a channel config-style alias.\n\n## User Impact\n\nNormal Slack users keep the default Slack API behavior. QA and integration harnesses can run Slack against a Slack-compatible mock API by setting SLACK_API_URL or passing slackApiUrl through the existing client option path.\n\nStack:\n- Slack foundation: this PR\n- WhatsApp foundation: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/97155\n- QA Lab Crabline wiring: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/95920\n\n## Evidence\n\n- node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/slack/src/client.test.ts extensions/slack/src/config-schema.test.ts\n- pnpm tsgo:extensions\n- git diff --check\n",
